I apologize for the confusion. To create a beam that fades out in length over time, you can use a similar approach to the one I outlined earlier for fading the beam's alpha value. Instead of updating the alpha value of the beam, you can adjust its end position to make it appear to shorten over time.

Here is an example of how you might accomplish this in your Half-Life plugin:

```pawn
#include <cstrike/beamflags>

#define BEAM_LENGTH_FADE_STEP 10 // Adjust to control fade speed
#define BEAM_LENGTH_FADE_DELAY 0.05 // Adjust to control fade update frequency

